==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hagdon
<hw>Hag"don</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧g"d⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of several species of sea birds of the genus
<gen>Puffinus</gen>; esp., <spn>Puffinus major</spn>, the greater
shearwarter, and <spn>Puffinus Stricklandi</spn>, the black hagdon or
sooty shearwater; -- called also <altname>hagdown</altname>,
<altname>haglin</altname>, and <altname>hag</altname>. See
<er>Shearwater</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hagfish</ent>⟦br⟧
